  <h>anthroponymic proper nouns</h>
  <p>Anthroponymic proper nouns are <a href="?xx=nouns/proper_nouns">proper nouns</a> which are also
      <a href="?xx=nouns/anthroponyms">anthroponyms</a> – nouns which identify individual persons
    (and other personified entities like toys, boats, pets). Examples of anthroponymic proper nouns
    are <g>Mairead</g>
    <fem/>
    <en>Margaret</en>, <g>Seumas</g>
    <masc/>
    <en>James</en>.</p>
  <p>Anthroponymic proper nouns contrast with <a href="?xx=nouns/anthroponymic_name_descriptions"
      >anthroponymic name-descriptions</a> like <g>An Caiptean</g>
    <en>The Captain</en> or <g>Bean Alasdair</g>
    <en>Alexander’s Wife</en>.</p>

  <section id="derivation">
    <h>derivation</h>
    <section>
      <h>simple</h>
      <p>The vast majority of anthroponymic proper nouns are simple, in that they are not (at least
        not obviously) created from other words.</p>
      <section id="fem">
        <h>feminine</h>
        <p><ul>
            <li><g>Anna</g><!--<a href="?gd=Anna"><g>Anna</g></a>-->
              <en>Anne</en></li>
            <li><g>Cairistìona</g>
              <en>Christine</en></li>
            <li><g>Caitrìona</g>
              <en>Catherine</en></li>
            <li><g>Ealasaid</g>
              <en>Elizabeth</en></li>
            <li><g>Eilidh</g>
              <en>Helen</en></li>
            <li><g>Mairead</g>
              <en>Margaret</en>, gen. <g>Maireid</g></li>
            <li><g>Màiri</g>
              <en>Mary</en></li>
            <li><g>Marsaili</g>
              <en>Marjory</en></li>
            <li><g>Mòr</g>
              <en>Sarah, Marion</en>, gen. <g>Mòir</g></li>
            <li><g>Oighrig</g>
              <en>Euphemia, Effie</en></li>
            <li><g>Raonaid</g>
              <en>Rachel</en>, also <g>Raghnaid</g></li>
            <li><g>Seònaid</g>
              <en>Janet</en></li>
            <li><g>Sìleas</g>
              <en>Julia, Cicely, Sheila</en>, gen. <g>Sìleis</g></li>
            <li><g>Sìne</g>
              <en>Joan</en></li>
          </ul></p>
      </section>
